{"type":"message-part","messageId":"07b9c1c5-684e-4192-aa83-d4afc5dc419d","role":"assistant","index":14,"part":{"type":"reasoning","text":"**Developing JWT Generation**\n\nI am now focusing on writing the Node.js script, `/home/user/myproject/generate_jwt.js`. The primary goal is to create a User JWT for MagicBell, utilizing the HMAC-HS256 algorithm for signing. I'll ensure all specified requirements are met.\n\n**Validating Environment Variables**\n\nI'm currently refining the script's robustness. My thought process is leaning towards implementing checks for all necessary environment variables (`MAGICBELL_SECRET_KEY`, `MAGICBELL_API_KEY`, `MAGICBELL_EMAIL`, `ZEALT_RUN_ID`). I'm considering whether to throw an explicit error if any are absent, ensuring a cleaner execution path.\n\n**Refining JWT Generation**\n\nI'm currently integrating the JWT generation logic into the Node.js script. My immediate focus is on ensuring the token is correctly signed with the `MAGICBELL_SECRET_KEY`, as explicitly stated in the requirements. I'm also solidifying the payload construction using the necessary environment variables.\n\n","state":"done"}}
{"type":"message-part","messageId":"07b9c1c5-684e-4192-aa83-d4afc5dc419d","role":"assistant","index":15,"part":{"type":"tool-writeToFile","toolCallId":"9MhKTMn47VmMLtWZ","state":"output-available","input":{"path":"/home/user/myproject/generate_jwt.js","content":"const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');\n\nconst apiKey = process.env.MAGICBELL_API_KEY;\nconst secretKey = process.env.MAGICBELL_SECRET_KEY;\nconst email = process.env.MAGICBELL_EMAIL;\nconst runId = process.env.ZEALT_RUN_ID;\n\nif (!apiKey || !secretKey || !email || !runId) {\n  console.error('Error: Missing required environment variables: MAGICBELL_API_KEY, MAGICBELL_SECRET_KEY, MAGICBELL_EMAIL, ZEALT_RUN_ID');\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\nconst userEmail = `${email}+${runId}@gmail.com`;\nconst userExternalId = `user_${runId}`;\n\nconst payload = {\n  user_email: userEmail,\n  user_external_id: userExternalId,\n  api_key: apiKey\n};\n\nconst token = jwt.sign(payload, secretKey, {\n  algorithm: 'HS256',\n  expiresIn: '1y'\n});\n\nconsole.log(`User JWT: ${token}`);\n"},"output":{"success":true},"callProviderMetadata":{"vertex":{"thoughtSignature":""}}}}
